⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 85/120 – Full Load ETL

🎤 Interview Question

You receive a complete employee dataset every day.

Write PySpark code to:

1. Read the source data.


2. Replace the target table with the latest dataset.




---

📊 Source Data
u4
emp_id	name	department	salary

101	John	IT	60000
102	Alice	HR	50000
103	Bob	Finance	70000



---

✅ Recommended Solution

source_df = spark.read.parquet("/source/employees")

source_df.write \
    .mode("overwrite") \
    .parquet("/target/employees")


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. What is a Full Load?

Answer

Every execution loads all records from the source and replaces the target.


---

Q2. When is Full Load preferred?

Answer

Small datasets

Initial data migration

Dimension tables with low volume



---

Q3. What is the drawback?

Answer

It is inefficient for large datasets because unchanged records are also reloaded.


