⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 86/120 – Incremental Load

🎤 Interview Question

The source table contains a last_updated column.

Load only records updated after the last successful ETL run.


---

📊 Source Data

emp_id	name	last_updated

101	John	2024-01-10
102	Alice	2024-03-01
103	Bob	2024-03-15


Last ETL Run:

2024-02-01


---

✅ Expected Output

emp_id	name

102	Alice
103	Bob



---

✅ Recommended Solution

from pyspark.sql.functions import col

last_run = "2024-02-01"

incremental_df = source_df.filter(
    col("last_updated") > last_run
)

incremental_df.show()


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. Why use Incremental Load?

Answer

It processes only new or changed records, reducing execution time and resource usage.


---

Q2. Which column is commonly used?

Answer

last_updated

modified_date

timestamp

audit columns



---

Q3. What if timestamps are missing?

Answer

Incremental loading becomes difficult. Many systems then rely on CDC or business keys.


