⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 87/120 – Change Data Capture (CDC)

🎤 Interview Question

You have:

Source Table

emp_id	salary

101	65000
102	50000
104	70000


Target Table

emp_id	salary

101	60000
102	50000
103	45000


Identify:

New records

Updated records

Deleted records



---

✅ Recommended Solution

from pyspark.sql.functions import col

# New Records
new_df = source_df.join(
    target_df,
    "emp_id",
    "left_anti"
)

# Deleted Records
deleted_df = target_df.join(
    source_df,
    "emp_id",
    "left_anti"
)

# Updated Records
updated_df = (
    source_df.alias("s")
    .join(target_df.alias("t"), "emp_id")
    .filter(col("s.salary") != col("t.salary"))
)


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. What are the three CDC operations?

Answer

Insert

Update

Delete



---

Q2. Which join is commonly used for new records?

Answer

left_anti


---

Q3. Why is CDC important?

Answer

It minimizes data movement by processing only changed records.


