⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 88/120 – SCD Type 1

🎤 Interview Question

Customer Address changes from:

Hyderabad

to

Bangalore

Implement SCD Type 1.


---

📊 Target Before

customer_id	city

101	Hyderabad



---

📊 Source

customer_id	city

101	Bangalore



---

✅ Expected Output

customer_id	city

101	Bangalore



---

✅ Recommended Solution

result = (
    target_df.alias("t")
    .join(source_df.alias("s"), "customer_id", "full")
    .select(
        col("customer_id"),
        col("s.city").alias("city")
    )
)

> In production environments (especially Delta Lake), this is commonly implemented using a MERGE statement rather than rebuilding the table manually.




---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. What is SCD Type 1?

Answer

The old value is overwritten with the new value. No history is maintained.


---

Q2. Is history preserved?

Answer

No.


---

Q3. Where is SCD Type 1 used?

Answer

Correcting spelling mistakes

Updating phone numbers

Updating email addresses

Non-historical reference data



